{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Add missing get_prs_max_dl_toa() function for PRS measurements\n\n### Summary\nUsers attempting to retrieve the maximum DL TOA from PRS measurements were encountering undefined behavior as the expected `get_prs_max_dl_toa()` function was not implemented in the codebase. This led to linker errors or runtime crashes when modules attempted to call this function.\n\nThe issue was resolved by implementing the missing `get_prs_max_dl_toa()` function in `nr_dl_channel_estimation.c` which iterates through all receive antennas for a given gNB and PRS resource to find the maximum `dl_toa` value. Proper error checking and logging were added to handle cases where PRS measurements are not initialized.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_UE_ESTIMATION/nr_estimation.h`: Added function declaration for `get_prs_max_dl_toa()`\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_UE_ESTIMATION/nr_dl_channel_estimation.c`: Implemented `get_prs_max_dl_toa()` function with parameter validation and maximum TOA calculation across all RX antennas\n"
}